&quot;Kyabar&#39;s Bite&quot;<br>
By: The Godless Magi  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The strategy behind this is to get Agrilla and Baldar out together. Build Baldar up and hurt your opponent by playing jagged rocks and adding to Baldar.Use Agrilla&#39;s power to allow Baldar to attack creatures with less energy twice doing no damage to Baldar, this can really hurt your opponent as you keep e5 creatures out of his defense. Keeping a mosp in play helps you build up your other creatures as it is the only creature that can be attacked when it is in play. I keep the Darges in play because it is a very strong anti-core card and at e6 it is a strong creature in itself.A cliff Hyren directs all spells and powers to itself, this helps you protect your Baldar and Agrilla. Use the Cragnoc&#39;s power to power up your mage and you still have an e5 creature in play. Gratch is great if you  can build him up (use jagged rocks) because if he is larger than the opponents largest creature each of your creatures gains one energy and if this condition exists and you have an XAMF in play add e4 to your magi!!!<br>
 Kybars scroll allows you to keep the cards you need in your hand.Relic stalkers help keep your relics in play and eliminate your opponents relics.Always keep a Climbing staff and a water of life relic in play, giving an extra two energy to your mage. With the high energy levels of your creatures this is very important.<br>
   Your spells weaken opponents and add e to your weaker creatures, Stone Storm and  Jagged rocks. Rock Slide costs e5 but eliminates the largest creature in play, be careful here because most of the time you will have the largest creature in play and YES you do kill yourself.<br>
   I usually specialize in a &quot;beat-down&quot; or &quot;build up&quot; deck but when this came out I found an awesome combination deck without having multiple regions.  Try it  you&#39;ll like it!!!<br>
<br>
